definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
to go against/to be contrary to/perverse/rebellious

sentences.english: Your method is against the domestic disciplines made by our forefathers.
sentences.chinese: 你的這種做法是有悖於祖宗家法的。

sentences.english: May go against the redistributional efforts of the government.
sentences.chinese: 可能有悖於政府的再分配努力。

sentences.english: A related worry is that of perverse incentives.
sentences.chinese: 另一個疑慮是有悖於常情的誘因。

sentences.english: A paradox it may be, but this was not an accident or a mistake.
sentences.chinese: 這種體制安排或許有悖於常理，但既非偶然亦非錯誤。

sentences.english: You may not like that, it may go against your intuition.
sentences.chinese: 你也許不喜歡這個結論，它有悖於你的直覺。

sentences.english: That goes against the custom of treating all sites neutrally.
sentences.chinese: 這有悖於所有網站中立對待的慣例。

sentences.english: And obviously any forms of corruption acts against that.
sentences.chinese: 很明顯，任何形式的腐敗行爲都有悖於此。
